sentences: Tommy Facenda (born November 10, 1939) is an American rock and roll singer and guitarist.
He is best known for his 1959 single "High School U.S.A."
Born in Portsmouth, Virginia, he joined Gene Vincent's Blue Caps in 1957, where he performed as a backup vocalist and was given the nickname "Bubba".
Facenda toured with Vincent and appeared in films with him, but by 1958 had left Vincent to seek a solo career.
The song became a nationwide hit, reaching No. 30 on the Rhythm and Blues chart and No. 28 on the Billboard Hot 100 in 1959.
He served in the military through 1962 and then worked as a firefighter in his hometown of Portsmouth.
He toured again with the Blue Caps beginning in 1982, and did some stage acting, performing in a play entitled Just Us.
In 2012, the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame inducted Facenda as a member of the Blue Caps by a special committee, aiming to correct the previous wrong of not including the Blue Caps with Gene Vincent.
"High School U.S.A." (National version) / "High School U.S.A." (Los Angeles Version) – Legrand 1001 (reissue)
Facenda wrote and recorded a 1960 followup single, "Bubba Ditty", which failed to chart.
"High School U.S.A." (National version) / "Give Me Another Chance" – Legrand 1001 – 1959
"High School U.S.A." (Regional versions, see below) / "Plea Of Love" – Atlantic 51–78 – 1959
